{{Infobox building | name = No. 6, Convent Place | logo = Coat of Arms of the Government of Gibraltar.svg | logo_size = 100 | image = No. 6 Convent Place and The Convent.jpg | caption = View of 6 Convent Place with [[The Convent (Gibraltar)|The Convent]] (the [[Governor of Gibraltar|Governor]]'s residence) in the background. | map_type = Gibraltar | map_caption = Location of 6 Convent Place in Gibraltar | coordinates = {{coord|36.1373|-5.3528|region:GI|display=inline,title}} | location_town = [[Gibraltar]] | location_country = {{flagicon|GIB}} Gibraltar | architect = | client = [[Chief Minister of Gibraltar]] | website = {{URL|http://www.gibraltar.gov.gi}} | engineer = | construction_start_date= | completion_date = | date_demolished = }}
'''6 Convent Place''', colloquially known in [[Gibraltar]] as "'''Number 6'''", is the [[headquarters]] of [[Government of Gibraltar|Her Majesty's Government of Gibraltar]] and the office of the [[Chief Minister of Gibraltar|Chief Minister]]. It is located opposite [[The Convent (Gibraltar)|The Convent]], the [[Governor of Gibraltar]]'s official residence.
Gibraltar's Economic Planning and Statistics Office is located in the building.<ref>{{cite book|title=Europe Review|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Hwi0s3I5jLEC&pg=PA152|accessdate=2 May 2013|year=2003|publisher=Kogan Page Publishers|isbn=978-0-7494-4067-1|page=152}}</ref>
