'''Interethnic marriage''' is a form of [[exogamy]] that involves a [[marriage]] between spouses who belong to different [[ethnic group]]s or [[Race (classification of human beings)|races]]. Intra-racial interethnic marriage was not historically a taboo in the [[United States]].<ref>[http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/18090277/ns/us_news-life/t/after-years-interracial-marriage-flourishing/ Interracial marriage flourishes in U.S. – US news – Life – Race & ethnicity]. MSNBC (2007-04-15). Retrieved 9 May 2012.</ref><ref name=HuffingtonHopeYen>Yen, Hope (2012-02-16). [http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/02/16/interracial-marriage-in-us_n_1281229.html Interracial marriage In the U.S. Climbs to New High, Study Finds]. Huffington Post</ref>

== Asia ==
=== China ===
During the [[Manchu people|Manchu]]-led [[Qing dynasty]] (1644–1912), Manchu and Han [[Identity in the Eight Banners|bannerwomen]] were punished if they married Han civilian men.

=== South Korea ===
In recent years, the number of interethnic marriages in Korea has increased substantially. However, most of Non-Korean spouses of Korean peoples are [[Asian people]]s.

