{{Same-sex marriage map South America|align=left}}
'''Lesbian, gay, bisexual, and transgender''' ([[LGBT]]) people in [[Piauí]],  a  [[States of Brazil|state]] of [[Brazil]] located in the country's [[Northeast Region, Brazil|Northeast Region]] enjoy  many of the same legal protections available to non-LGBT people. Homosexuality is legal in the state.

==Recognition of same-sex marriages==
*On December 14, 2012, the Court of [[Piauí]] began granting same-sex couples marriage licenses through all notaries statewide, thus ending a long struggle for marriage equality in state. Now, couples do not need to have a judge's approval to get married. This change was published officially in the 'Diário do Justiça' of this state on December 17, 2012.<ref>[http://diariodeteresina.com.br/chamadas/corregedoria-do-tj-regulamenta-casamento-gay-no-piaui/#.UNEVbuSZmSo Casamento gay no PI/Same-sex marriage in PI<!-- Bot generated title --> {{pt icon}}]</ref>

