{{for|the fictional superhero team|Supreme Soviets}}
The '''Supreme Soviet''' ({{lang-ru|Верховный Совет}}, ''Verkhovny Sovet'', {{lang-en|literally "Supreme Council"}}) was the common name for the [[legislative bodies]] (parliaments) of the [[Soviet socialist republic]]s (SSR) in the [[Union of Soviet Socialist Republics]] (USSR). These soviets were modeled after the [[Supreme Soviet of the USSR]], established in 1938, and were nearly identical.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=XAItI5C_JPUC&pg=PA70&as_brr=3&client=firefox-a#v=onepage&f=false Where nation-states come from: institutional change in the age of nationalism by Philip G. Roeder, p. 70]</ref> Soviet-approved delegates to the Supreme Soviets were periodically elected in unopposed elections.<ref name=huber>[https://books.google.com/books?id=s5H902xXOXEC&pg=PA52&as_brr=3&client=firefox-a#v=onepage&f=false Perestroika-era politics: the new Soviet legislature and Gorbachev's political reforms by Robert T. Huber and Donald R. Kelley, p. 52]</ref> The first free or semi-free elections took place during ''[[perestroika]]'' in late 1980s. The soviets until then were largely [[Rubber stamp (politics)|rubber-stamp]] institutions, approving decisions handed to them by the [[Communist Party of the USSR]] or of each SSR.<ref name=huber/> The soviets met infrequently (often only twice a year for only several days) and elected the [[Presidium of the Supreme Soviet]], a permanent body, to act on their behalf while the soviet was not in session.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=JWt7MN3Dch8C&pg=PA192&as_brr=3&client=firefox-a#v=onepage&q=&f=false Russian law: the end of the Soviet system and the role of law by Ferdinand Joseph Maria Feldbrugge, p. 192]</ref> Under the [[1936 Soviet Constitution|1936]] and [[1977 Soviet Constitution]]s the Presidium of the Supreme Soviet served as the [[Head of state#Multiple or collective heads of state|collective head of state]] of the USSR.<ref> {{Cite book |url= https://books.google.sk/books?id=ZH9nkBOxrZQC&pg=PA165&dq=presidium+of+the+supreme+soviet+collective+head+of+state&hl=cs&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj1lb3F_cXQAhVKBsAKHcNmBysQ6AEINTAE#v=onepage&q=presidium%20of%20the%20supreme%20soviet%20collective%20head%20of%20state&f=false |title= Ideology, Politics, and Government in the Soviet Union: An Introduction– Google Knihy |publisher= Books.google.cz |date= January 1, 1978|accessdate= 2016-11-26 }} </ref> The Supreme Soviets also elected the [[Council of Ministers of the Soviet Union | Council of Ministers]], an executive body. After the [[dissolution of the USSR]] in late December 1991, most of these soviets became the legislatures of independent countries.
== Supreme Soviets of the Soviet Republics == *{{flag|Russian SFSR}}: [[Supreme Soviet of Russia|Верховный Совет РСФСР]] *{{flag|Ukrainian SSR|name=Ukraine}}: [[Verkhovna Rada#Before independence|Верховна Рада Української РСР]] *{{flag|Byelorussian SSR|name=Byelorussia}}: [[Supreme Soviet of Belarus|Вярхоўны Савет Беларускай ССР]] *{{flag|Uzbek SSR|name=Uzbekistan}}: Ўзбекистон ССР Олий Совети ''(O'zbekiston SSR Oliy Soveti)'' *{{flag|Kazakh SSR|name=Kazakhstan}}: Қазақ КСР-нiң Жоғарғы Кеңесi *{{flag|Georgian SSR|name=Georgia}}: [[Supreme Soviet of Georgia|საქართველოს სსრ უმაღლესი საბჭო]] *{{flag|Azerbaijan SSR|name=Azerbaijan}}: [[Supreme Soviet of Azerbaijan SSR|Азәрбаjҹан ССР Али Совети]] ''(Azәrbaycan SSR Ali Soveti)'' *{{flag|Lithuanian SSR|name=Lithuania}}: [[Supreme Soviet of the Lithuanian SSR|Lietuvos TSR Aukščiausioji Taryba]] *{{flag|Moldavian SSR|name=Moldavia}}: Совиетул Супрем ал РСС Молдовеняскэ ''(Sovietul Suprem al RSS Moldovenească)'' *{{flag|Latvian SSR|name=Latvia}}: Latvijas PSR Augstākā Padome *{{flag|Kirghiz SSR|name=Kirghizia}}: Кыргыз ССР Жогорку Совети *{{flag|Tajik SSR|name=Tajikistan}}: [[Supreme Soviet of the Tajik SSR|Совети Олӣ РСС Тоҷикистон]] *{{flag|Armenian SSR|name=Armenia}}: [[Supreme Soviet of Armenia|Հայկական ՍՍՀ Գերագույն Խորհուրդ]] *{{flag|Turkmen SSR|name=Turkmenistan}}: Түркменистан ССР Ёкары Советы ''(Turkmenistan SSR Ýokary Sowety)'' *{{flag|Estonian SSR|name=Estonia}}: Eesti NSV Ülemnõukogu
